Finance Minister Dilson Funaro,currently on a global tour to seek governmental support for hisefforts to solve Brazil's 108 billion dlrs foreign debt crisis,said creditors have expressed willingness to help.    In an interview with the Globo television network,transmitted from Rome, Funaro said he had proposed a "four-yearplan" to the creditors, which would include a rescaling of thecommitments derived from its debt.    After visiting the U.S., England, France, West Germany,Italy and Switzerland, Funaro is now on his way to Tokyo, wherehe is to arrive on Sunday for talks with Japanese governmentofficials as well as private bankers. Reuter&#3;